 "cells": [

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Tutorial 7 - Transformations of 1D FEP and kinetics"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Introduction"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In this notebook, we investigate the impact of the choice of the collective variable on the free energy profile as well as the kinetics. The main conclusion of this notebook will be that the shape of the free energy profile depends on the choice of the CV (as well as for example the difference in free energy between the reactant state minimum and the transition state maximum), however, the derived kinetic rate constant (and hence also the related phenomenological free energy barrier) will not depend on this choice."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%load_ext autoreload\n",
    "%autoreload 2"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from thermolib.thermodynamics.fep import SimpleFreeEnergyProfile, plot_profiles\n",
    "from thermolib.thermodynamics.histogram import Histogram1D\n",
    "from thermolib.tools import read_wham_input, blav, decorrelate\n",
    "from thermolib.thermodynamics.trajectory import ColVarReader\n",
    "from thermolib.thermodynamics.cv import CoordinationNumber, LinearCombination, FunctionCV\n",
    "from thermolib.kinetics.rate import RateFactorEquilibrium\n",
    "\n",
    "import numpy as np, os\n",
    "\n",
    "from molmod.units import *"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "prefix = 'advanced_wham1D_transformations_'"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## FEP and rate with original CV"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We start be constructing the reference FEP in terms of the original CV, i.e. the CV along which the biasing was performed."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "bins = np.arange(-1.7, 1.7, 0.02)\n",
    "fn_meta = 'data/formic_acid_dimer_link/wham_input.txt'"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "colvar_reader = ColVarReader([0], units=['au'])\n",
    "temp, biasses, trajectories = read_wham_input(\n",
    "    fn_meta, colvar_reader, 'colvars/COLVAR_%s.dat', \n",
    "    bias_potential='Parabola1D', q01_unit='au', kappa1_unit='kjmol',\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We decorrelate the data using the built-in `decorrelate` routine from the `thermolib.tools` module..."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "/home/louis/miniconda3/lib/python3.8/site-packages/scipy/optimize/minpack.py:828: OptimizeWarning: Covariance of the parameters could not be estimated\n",
      "  warnings.warn('Covariance of the parameters could not be estimated',\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 0 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 576x432 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "corrtimes = decorrelate(trajectories, plot=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "...and construct the corresponding FEP"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "SCF Converged!\n",
      "---------------------------------------------------------------------\n",
      "TIMING SUMMARY\n",
      "  initializing: 00h 00m 00.000s\n",
      "  histograms  : 00h 00m 00.067s\n",
      "  bias poten. : 00h 00m 00.013s\n",
      "  solve scf   : 00h 00m 00.324s\n",
      "  error est.  : 00h 00m 00.034s\n",
      "  TOTAL       : 00h 00m 00.439s\n",
      "---------------------------------------------------------------------\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "findfont: Font family ['sans-serif'] not found. Falling back to DejaVu Sans.\n",
      "findfont: Font family ['sans-serif'] not found. Falling back to DejaVu Sans.\n",
      "findfont: Font family ['sans-serif'] not found. Falling back to DejaVu Sans.\n",
      "findfont: Font family ['sans-serif'] not found. Falling back to DejaVu Sans.\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1152x576 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "hist = Histogram1D.from_wham(bins, trajectories, biasses, temp, error_estimate='mle_f_cov', corrtimes=corrtimes, Nscf=10000)\n",
    "fep = SimpleFreeEnergyProfile.from_histogram(hist, temp=temp)\n",
    "fep.process_states(lims=[-1.55,-0.2,0.2,1.55])\n",
    "fep.set_ref(ref='r')\n",
    "fep.plot()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "vscode": {
     "languageId": "raw"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "We now also proceed by computing the rate constant according to this CV choice. For this we use all settings as discussed in the [tutorial on basic kinetics](basic_kinetics.html)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#CV definition\n",
    "C1 = CoordinationNumber([[0,9]], r0=1.4*angstrom)\n",
    "C2 = CoordinationNumber([[7,9]], r0=1.4*angstrom)\n",
    "C3 = CoordinationNumber([[2,4]], r0=1.4*angstrom)\n",
    "C4 = CoordinationNumber([[5,4]], r0=1.4*angstrom)\n",
    "CV = LinearCombination([C1,C2,C3,C4], [1., -1., -1., 1.])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "CV_TS_Delta = 0.05\n",
    "CV_TS_lims = [fep.ts.get_cv()-CV_TS_Delta, fep.ts.get_cv()+CV_TS_Delta]\n",
    "rate = RateFactorEquilibrium(CV, CV_TS_lims, temp, CV_unit='au')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "fn = '%s/colvars/u64.xyz' %os.path.dirname(fn_meta)\n",
    "rate.process_trajectory(fn, finish=False, momenta='analytical')\n",
    "rate.finish()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Rate factor with block averaging:\n",
      "---------------------------------\n",
      "  A = 17.457 +- 0.011 1e12*au/s (8734 TS samples, int. autocorr. time = 17.289 timesteps)\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1152x576 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "A, A_dist = rate.result_blav()\n",
    "rate_results = rate.compute_rate(fep)\n",
    "fep.plot(rate=rate)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## FEP and rate in terms of alternative CV"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We are going to transform the FEP from $F(CV)$ towards $F(Q)$ with $Q=\\frac{1}{0.9}e^{0.9\\cdot CV}$. This can be done using the ``transform`` routine of the BaseFreeEnergyProfile class (as well as it child class SimpleFreeEnergyProfile). For that, we first derive the transformation function as well as its derivative:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def function(cv):\n",
    "    return np.exp(0.9*cv)\n",
    "\n",
    "def derivative(cv):\n",
    "    return 0.9*np.exp(0.9*cv)"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "fep2 = fep.transform_function(function, derivative=derivative)\n",
    "fep2.process_states(lims=[-np.inf,0.9,1.4,4.4])\n",
    "#fep2.set_ref(ref='r')\n",
    "fep2.plot(flims=[-5,30])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We clearly see that the free energy profile is not the same anymore as before. We now compute the rate according to the transformed CV and see if that has changed. For this, we use the CollectiveVariable child class ``FunctionCV`` to define a function of another CV:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "Q = FunctionCV(CV, function, derivative)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We will need to translate the limits on the TS region in CV space given by\n",
    "\n",
    "\\begin{align}\n",
    "    CV^{TS}_{lims} = [CV^{TS}-dCV,CV^{TS}+dCV]\n",
    "\\end{align}\n",
    "\n",
    "to the limits in Q space using the transformation function $Q=f(CV)$ and its derivative $f'(CV)$, which we do as follows:\n",
    "\n",
    "\\begin{align}\n",
    "    Q^{TS}_{lims} &= [Q^{TS}-dQ,Q^{TS}+dQ] \\\\\n",
    "    Q^{TS} &= f(CV^{TS}) \\\\\n",
    "    dQ &= f'(CV^{TS})\\cdot dCV\n",
    "\\end{align}"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "[0.987678610366878, 1.0768080481533355]\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "Q_TS_Delta = derivative(fep.ts.get_cv())*CV_TS_Delta\n",
    "Q_TS_lims = [fep2.ts.get_cv()-Q_TS_Delta, fep2.ts.get_cv()+Q_TS_Delta]\n",
    "print(Q_TS_lims)\n",
    "rate2 = RateFactorEquilibrium(Q, Q_TS_lims, temp, CV_unit='au')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Estimating rate factor from trajectory data/formic_acid_dimer_link/colvars/u64.xyz for TS=[0.988,1.077] au using analytical momentum integration\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fn = '%s/colvars/u64.xyz' %os.path.dirname(fn_meta)\n",
    "rate2.process_trajectory(fn, finish=False, momenta='analytical', verbose=True)\n",
    "rate2.finish()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [

      "---------------------------------\n",
      "  A = 15.969 +- 0.022 1e12*au/s (8670 TS samples, int. autocorr. time = 6.718 timesteps)\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    },
    {

      "image/png": "",

     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "A2, A2_dist = rate2.result_blav()\n",
    "rate2_results = rate2.compute_rate(fep2)\n",
    "fep2.plot(rate=rate2,flims=[-5,30])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "As we can see, the phenomenological barriers (both forward and backward) remain consistent with those computed with the original CV."
   ]
  }
